Not only did the wolf not threaten to huff and puff and blow the door down, but neither the wolf, nor anyone else, would go anywhere near the place. This little pig became depressed. He had no friends, because he was a pig who lived in a house made of depleted uranium. What a lonely existence he faced. The 92nd little pig woke up every day to the same disappointing life. He thought of ending it all, but he was passionate about the cause he had protested against so many times. He would not do anything to support baconism. The baconists would not have him for breakfast, not today and not ever.
